Dear Tamar and Adam

As per my email earlier, please find below and attached more information re=
garding the requested High Net Worth statement.
Hopefully you can send this to your UK accountant for them to complete.

The Statement of High Net Worth is a Consumer Credit Act requirement for le=
nding to UK residents and instructions for completion are also included bel=
ow. There is no scope for the statement to be completed in any way other th=
an as detailed.

The Statement of HNW is the prescribed statutory form, and should be printe=
d on the accountants firms headed paper and signed by an individual account=
ant who is a member of one of the relevant professional bodies.  The form s=
hould be printed on their firm paper but it should be signed by the individ=
ual and not in the name or capacity of their firm.  The accountant needs to=
 note which relevant professional body applies to them and their membership=
 number.

A list of acceptable professional bodies is included below:

(a) the Institute of Chartered Accountants in England and Wales;
(b) the Institute of Chartered Accountants of Scotland;
(c) the Institute of Chartered Accounts in Ireland;
(d) the Association of Chartered Certified Accountants;
(e) the Chartered Institute of Management Accountants;
(f) the Chartered Institute of Public Finance and Accountancy;
(g) a professional body for accountants established in a jurisdiction outsi=
de the United Kingdom.

Kind regards
Loicque

Lo=EFcque Windey
